My School Hub - Codex Context
Last updated: 2026-04-28

System summary
- Multi-tenant SaaS school management platform by Tishanyq Digital.
- Core stack: React 19 + Vite 7 frontend, Django 5.2 + DRF backend, optional Go gateway/workers/services.
- Main domains: academics, attendance, report cards, boarding, finance/payments, HR/staff, library, messaging, audit/compliance.

Architecture
- Frontend: `src/` (role-based pages, centralized API client in `src/services/apiService.jsx`).
- Backend: `School_system/` Django project.
  - Apps: `users`, `academics`, `finances`, `staff`, `library`, `whatsapp_intergration`.
- API base path: `/api/v1/`.
- Docs: `/api/v1/docs/`.

Roles supported
- `superadmin`, `admin`, `teacher`, `student`, `parent`, `hr`, `accountant`, `security`, `cleaner`, `librarian`, `sports_director`.

Key backend mounts
- `/api/v1/auth/`
- `/api/v1/academics/`
- `/api/v1/students/`
- `/api/v1/teachers/`
- `/api/v1/parents/`
- `/api/v1/messages/`
- `/api/v1/boarding/`
- `/api/v1/finances/`
- `/api/v1/staff/`
- `/api/v1/library/`

Multi-tenancy and access model
- Tenant isolation is school-based (`school` FK across domain data).
- Permission controls include role checks plus HR/accountant page-level profiles.
- Root HR capability is represented via `HRPermissionProfile.is_root_boss`.

Attendance model (current)
- Daily attendance: `ClassAttendance` (class teacher marks per day).
- Lesson/period attendance: `SubjectAttendance` (teacher marks per class/subject/date, now supports period metadata).
- Statuses: `present`, `absent`, `late`, `excused`.

Recent attendance enhancements (implemented)
- `SubjectAttendance` now includes:
  - `period_number`, `period_label`
  - `marked_with_permission`
  - `bunk_flag`, `bunk_reason`
- New `AttendancePermission` model for approved absences (day-level or period-level).
- New school setting on `SchoolSettings`:
  - `attendance_period_tracking_start_date`
  - Purpose: start applying period-bunk logic from a chosen date without rewriting historical data.

Bunk detection logic
- Applies only when `attendance_date >= attendance_period_tracking_start_date`.
- A period can be flagged bunked when:
  - period status is `absent`,
  - no approved permission exists,
  - daily class status is `present` or `late`.

Attendance admin/HR controls
- Admin/HR can configure tracking start date:
  - `POST /api/v1/academics/attendance/period-tracking-start-date/`
- Admin/HR can manage permissions:
  - `GET/POST /api/v1/academics/attendance/permissions/`
- Admin/HR can edit locked attendance records:
  - `PATCH /api/v1/academics/attendance/class/<attendance_id>/edit/`
  - `PATCH /api/v1/academics/attendance/subject/<attendance_id>/edit/`

Frontend API methods available
- `setAttendancePeriodTrackingStartDate(startDate)`
- `getAttendancePermissions(params)`
- `createAttendancePermission(data)`
- `editClassAttendance(attendanceId, data)`
- `editSubjectAttendance(attendanceId, data)`
- Note: methods exist in `apiService.jsx`; visible admin UI wiring may still be pending.

Operational notes
- Run migrations after pull/change:
  - `cd School_system`
  - `python manage.py migrate`
- If env has non-boolean `DEBUG` values (e.g., `release`), use explicit override for manage.py commands:
  - `DEBUG=False python manage.py <command>`

